{{Wikipedia|Degenerate (humans)}}
== English ==
=== Adjective ===
'''degenerate'''
# having [[degenerated]]; being in a degenerated state
# A situation in which multiple [[case]]s [[correspond]] to one state.
#: ''The [[genetic code]] is degenerate because a single amino acid can be coded by one of several [[codon|codons]].
# as it pertains to [[human]]s means the [[physical]], [[mental]] or [[moral]] qualities that are considered [[normal]], [[coherent]], [[balanced]] and  [[desire|desirable]] have [[deteriorate]]d, [[degrade]]d or fallen from excellence to a lower state.

===Intransitive verb===
'''to degenerate'''
# to [[lose]] good or [[desirable]] [[quality|qualities]]
#: ''His condition continued to '''degenerate''' even after admission to hospital.''

